# Invariants & contracts
  @invariant  render + input only — holds wv only, never wm/rm; all queries/mutations go through wv.  @ 3
  @invariant  renderer owns every pixel — geometry, port layout, hit-tests. See docs/wiringPage.md  @ 4
  @invariant  wires draw as a pre-pass before nodes — centre-to-centre lines occluded by the bodies; parallel wires in one unordered pair are offset perpendicularly, MIDI sorted to the right.  @ 5
  @invariant  port rows are top/bottom only. See docs/wiringPage.md § The port band.  @ 6
  @invariant  key bindings + wiring-scope command bodies live here; coord pushes scope on activation.  @ 7
  @contract  wiringPage (the controller) owns the stack (rm/wm/wv) and hands this renderer wv only  @ 8

